---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="@maplibre-yaml/astro — minimal example">
  <main>
    <h1>@maplibre-yaml/astro — minimal example</h1>
    <p>
      A bare Astro app demonstrating <code>@maplibre-yaml/astro</code>: GeoJSON
      feature references, content-collection map dispatch, and direct builder
      use. No styling frameworks, no extra integrations — just the API.
    </p>

    <h2>Demos</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="/showcase">Feature-ref showcase</a> — every GeoJSON geometry
        type plus edge cases, error scenarios, and override precedence.
        Each section maps 1:1 to a checkbox in
        <code>testing-criteria-pr20.md</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/poas/sample">Content collection example</a> — a single
        markdown entry with a <code>feature_ref</code>, rendered via
        <code>buildMapConfigFromEntry</code>.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How this example is wired</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Global map config: <code>src/config/maps.yaml</code> loaded by
        <code>loadGlobalMapConfig</code> in <code>src/lib/map-config.ts</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Fixture: <code>src/data/sample.geojson</code> — 11 features covering
        Point, MultiPoint, LineString, MultiLineString, Polygon, MultiPolygon,
        GeometryCollection (single inner + heterogeneous), 3D coords, no-properties,
        and a degenerate-line edge case.
      </li>
      <li>
        Content collection: <code>src/content/poas/</code> with
        <code>getCollectionItemWithFeatureRefSchema</code> (strict XOR between
        <code>feature_ref</code> and inline geometry).
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Run locally</h2>
    <pre>cd examples/astro/minimal
pnpm install
pnpm dev</pre>
  </main>
</Layout>
